02:10.300 --> 02:11.600
(Daniel) WOW.
(Amanda) YEAH.

02:11.600 --> 02:13.900
THAT'S IT?
THOSE ARE
THE D.N.A. RESULTS.

02:13.900 --> 02:16.400
SO, UH, H-HOW MANY TIMES
DO YOU THINK WE...

02:16.400 --> 02:18.300
<i>ALOT, BUT JUST REMEMBER,</i>

02:18.300 --> 02:20.000
IF YOUR DAD'S D.N.A.
DOES MATCH MINE,

02:20.000 --> 02:21.700
WE'RE ONLY HALF BROTHER
AND SISTER,

02:21.700 --> 02:23.700
WHICH MEANS IF WE DID IT,
LIKE, 20 TIMES,

02:23.700 --> 02:27.000
IT WAS ONLY WRONG TEN.
OKAY, THAT ACTUALLY
MADE SENSE TO ME.

02:27.500 --> 02:30.600
<i>YOU ARE SO MY SISTER.
OH, MY GOD.
I CAN'T TAKE IT ANYMORE.</i>

02:34.600 --> 02:36.500
(gasps)
BRADFORD'S NOT MY FATHER!
YOU'RE NOT MY SISTER?

02:38.000 --> 02:40.200
KISSING ISN'T WEIRD AT ALL.
IT'S GREAT.
WE'RE NOT RELATED.

02:40.200 --> 02:41.700
WE COULD KISS ALL WE WANT,
RIGHT?

02:41.700 --> 02:43.100
YEAH,
WE CAN TOTALLY DO THIS.

02:45.300 --> 02:46.700
NOTHING TABOO HERE.

02:46.700 --> 02:49.000
(giggles)
YOU KNOW WHAT?
WHY DON'T WE HOP IN--

02:49.000 --> 02:53.200
DANIEL, NO. I HAVE
UNRESOLVED ISSUES WITH YOU.

02:53.800 --> 02:56.000
SO JUST SQUEEZE A BOOB,
BECAUSE I HAVE TO GO.

03:00.200 --> 03:03.200
OH, MY GOD.
THIS IS SO HUMILIATING.

03:03.800 --> 03:05.300
I'VE NEVER DONE THIS BEFORE.

03:05.300 --> 03:06.400
TRY THIS.

03:06.400 --> 03:10.500
IT'S TOMATO JUICE, RAW EGG
AND A LITTLE BACON GREASE...

03:12.000 --> 03:13.400
A TRICK I LEARNED
IN HIGH SCHOOL.

03:13.400 --> 03:15.100
HANGOVER GONE
BY THIRD PERIOD.

03:20.100 --> 03:21.600
TASTES AS GOOD AS IT SOUNDS.

03:21.600 --> 03:22.900
SORRY WE DIDN'T
TAKE YOUR SHOES OFF

03:22.900 --> 03:24.500
BEFORE YOU WENT
TO BED LAST NIGHT,

03:24.500 --> 03:26.900
BUT WE COULD NOT UNTIE
THOSE DOUBLE KNOTS.

03:26.900 --> 03:28.400
I WORRY ABOUT TRIPPING.

03:29.400 --> 03:31.700
SO YOU MUST BE DYING
TO CALL THAT BITCH.

03:31.700 --> 03:32.700
CHARLIE?

03:34.400 --> 03:35.700
HONESTLY, I'M AFRAID TO.

03:36.200 --> 03:38.200
I DON'T KNOW WHAT I'M GONNA DO
WHEN I HEAR HER VOICE.

03:38.800 --> 03:40.600
I' NEVER BEEN THIS MAD.

03:40.600 --> 03:41.800
THIS IS YOU MAD?

03:42.900 --> 03:43.600
YEAH.

03:44.300 --> 03:46.100
I FEEL LIKE
A FEMALE ORANGUTAN

03:46.100 --> 03:47.200
WHEN SHE'S IN ESTROUS

03:47.200 --> 03:49.300
AND A NONDOMINANT MALE
TRIES TO MOUNT HER.

03:50.000 --> 03:52.800
SHE JUST BARES HER FANGS
AND ATTACKS BLINDLY.

03:54.300 --> 03:55.600
THAT STORY
WOULD BE MORE EFFECTIVE

03:55.600 --> 03:58.200
IF YOU COMPARED YOURSELF
TO THE MALE ORANGUTAN,

03:59.100 --> 04:00.900
AND IF I KNEW
WHAT ESTROUS WAS.

04:01.700 --> 04:02.500
YOU HUNGRY?

04:02.500 --> 04:03.100
OH! OH.

04:04.700 --> 04:07.000
I'M GLAD YOU'RE NOT MAD AT ME
FOR SPILLING THE BEANS.

04:07.000 --> 04:08.700
HE HAD TO FIND OUT SOMEHOW,
RIGHT?

04:08.700 --> 04:12.100
YEAH. SO WHAT ???? 
 I DON'T KNOW. 

04:12.100 --> 04:14.200
WAIT,
TRY NOT TO THINK ABOUT IT,

04:14.200 --> 04:15.800
WHICH IS EASY,
BECAUSE I HAVE SO MUCH TO DO

04:15.800 --> 04:16.800
FOR THIS BENEFIT TONIGHT.

04:16.800 --> 04:19.200
OH, PLEASE, DON'T TALK TO ME
ABOUT THE BLACK & WHITE BALL.

04:19.200 --> 04:22.500
I HAVE BEEN GLUING CRAP
ONTO THESE THINGS FOR TWO WEEKS.

04:22.500 --> 04:24.400
GLITTER CAME OUT IN MY PEE
YESTERDAY.

04:24.400 --> 04:26.100
YEAH,
BUT IT'S ALL FOR CHARITY,

04:26.100 --> 04:27.900
AND IT'S DANIEL'S
FAVORITE EVENT OF THE YEAR.

04:27.900 --> 04:29.600
HE GETS TO GO UP ONSTAGE
AND PRESENT

04:29.600 --> 04:31.700
THAT GIANT CHECK THINGY.

04:31.700 --> 04:34.600
YEAH, MEN GET EXCITED ABOUT
THINGS LIKE THAT, DON'T THEY?

04:35.800 --> 04:37.300
(bell tinkles)
OH, YAY! THE SANDWICH GUY!

04:41.100 --> 04:42.400
I GOT TOO EXCITED, RIGHT?

04:42.400 --> 04:43.600
WELL, MAYBE.

04:44.900 --> 04:47.800
OKAY, CHICKEN AND CHEESE SPECIAL
ON A BAGUETTE.

04:47.800 --> 04:50.800
NO CHICKEN, NO CHEESE,
NO BAGUETTE.

04:53.200 --> 04:55.900
I JUST SOLD HER
A PLATE OF LETTUCE FOR 7 BUCKS.

04:55.900 --> 04:58.200
<i>YES, BUT THAT'S HER BREAKFAST,
LUNCH AND DINNER,</i>

04:58.200 --> 05:00.100
SO REALLY, IT'S A BARGAIN.
MM.

05:00.100 --> 05:02.500
COULD I PLEASE GET
THE TURKEY SUN-DRIED TOMATO

05:02.500 --> 05:06.500
ON A BAGUETTE, PLEASE?
YES! MAN,
I KNEW YOU WERE AN EATER.

05:07.600 --> 05:09.300
OH. THANK YOU...

05:09.600 --> 05:10.500
I GUESS.

05:11.100 --> 05:13.300
SO YOU'RE NEW.
WHAT HAPPENED TO ROBERT?

05:13.300 --> 05:15.200
YOU KNOW,
I THINK HE INHERITED MONEY...

05:16.000 --> 05:17.200
OR WAS ARRESTED.

05:17.200 --> 05:18.000
OH.

05:18.000 --> 05:20.900
I DON'T KNOW. THERE WAS
A LAWYER AND CASH INVOLVED.

05:21.900 --> 05:23.500
WELL, WELCOME.

05:24.900 --> 05:28.100
HEY, BETTY. CAN YOU GET ME THIS
FOR THE, UH, BENEFIT TONIGHT?

05:29.100 --> 05:31.700
UH, OKAY, YES. THANK YOU.

05:32.200 --> 05:33.300
DANIEL!

05:33.800 --> 05:35.800
THE iBOT
MOTORIZED WHEELCHAIR?

05:35.800 --> 05:37.700
I THOUGHT YOU WERE SUPPOSED
TO BE WALKING BY TODAY

05:37.700 --> 05:39.600
NO, I STILL NEED THERAPY.

05:39.600 --> 05:41.500
I'M
STILL IN A LOT OF PAIN, BETTY.

05:41.500 --> 05:42.500
THANKS.

05:42.800 --> 05:44.600
OK, I KNOW
THAT YOU FEEL REALLY BAD

05:44.600 --> 05:46.900
ABOUT THIS WHOLE
ALEXIS THING...

05:46.900 --> 05:48.600
BUT DO YOU THINK
MAYBE YOUR PAIN

05:48.600 --> 05:50.700
COULD BE MORE EMOTIONAL
THAN PHYSICAL?

05:50.700 --> 05:53.100
MY LEG ISN'T CRYING, BETTY.
IT'S HURTING.

05:53.100 --> 05:54.900
JUST GET ME THE WHEELCHAIR,
OKAY?

05:54.900 --> 05:58.400
OKAY, I'LL JUST ADD IT
TO MY LIST.
OH, AND ABOUT THE CHECK.

05:58.400 --> 05:59.900
CAN YOU, UM, MAKE SURE
THE CHECK IS BIG,

05:59.900 --> 06:02.300
BUT NOT SO BIG IT MAKES
MY HEAD LOOK SMALL?
OKAY.

06:02.300 --> 06:06.500
AND IT SHOULD BE...
(clears throat) BLUE OR GREEN.

06:06.500 --> 06:09.000
BLUE. GOT IT.
SEE, 'CAUSE LAST YEAR,
IT WAS BEIGE,

06:09.000 --> 06:11.200
AND IN ALL THE PHOTOS,
I WAS KINDA WASHED OUT.

06:11.500 --> 06:13.500
WHATEVER YOU NEED.

06:13.900 --> 06:15.200
(telephone rings)
DANIEL MEADE'S OFFICE.

06:15.200 --> 06:17.200
<i>FASHION GIVES BACK--</i>

06:17.200 --> 06:19.400
<i>ONCE AGAIN, IT'S
THE "MODE" BLACK & WHITE BALL</i>

06:19.400 --> 06:21.600
<i>BENEFITING
NEW YORK CHILDREN'S HOSPITAL.</i>

06:21.600 --> 06:23.600
<i>YES, THE CLOTHES
WILL BE FABULOUS</i>

06:23.600 --> 06:25.800
<i>AND THE KIDS WILL BE SICK.</i>

06:26.600 --> 06:29.500
<i>UNFORTUNATELY, THIS YEAR,
CLAIRE MEADE WILL NOT BE ABLE</i>

06:29.500 --> 06:31.100
<i>TO FULFILL
HER USUAL HOSTESS DUTIES</i>

06:31.100 --> 06:33.800
<i>AS SHE'S ON THE LAM,
WHICH, I UNDERSTAND,</i>

06:33.800 --> 06:36.600
<i>IS WHAT MARIO BATALI
IS SERVING AS THE MAIN COURSE.</i>

06:36.600 --> 06:38.500
<i>BUT IN THE SPIRIT
OF BLACK & WHITE, </i>

06:38.500 --> 06:41.000
<i>THE BALL WILL BE PRESIDED
OVER BY BRADFORD MEADE</i>

06:41.000 --> 06:42.600
<i>AND FIANCÉE WILHELMINA SLATER.</i>

06:42.600 --> 06:45.000
<i>OR SHOULD I SAY EX-FIANCÉE?</i>

06:45.000 --> 06:47.100
<i>SINCE APPARENTLY, THE WEDDING
HAS BEEN POSTPONED.</i>

06:47.100 --> 06:49.200
<i>TROUBLE IN PARADISE?</i>
TURN IT OFF.

06:49.200 --> 06:51.800
UGH.
THIS IS SO HUMILIATING.

06:51.800 --> 06:53.800
MY CLOSEST FRIENDS IN THE WORLD
WILL BE THERE TONIGHT.

06:53.800 --> 06:56.000
CAN YOU IMAGINE HOW HAPPY
THIS IS GONNA MAKE THEM?

06:56.000 --> 06:59.200
OH! IT'S JUST
A TEMPORARY SETBACK.

06:59.700 --> 07:01.200
YOU'LL STILL HAVE THE WEDDING
IN A FEW MONTHS.

07:01.200 --> 07:03.100
IF BRADFORD THINKS
HE LOVES YOU NOW,

07:03.100 --> 07:05.600
HE'LL THINK
HE LOVES YOU THEN.
THE LONGER WE WAIT,

07:05.600 --> 07:09.100
THE MORE TIME BRADFORD'S SPAWN
WILL HAVE TO TALK HIM OUT OF IT.

07:10.000 --> 07:11.700
(sighs)
I'M DONE, MARC. IT'S OVER.

07:11.700 --> 07:13.300
NOW YOU LISTEN TO ME, LADY.

07:13.300 --> 07:15.800
THE WILHELMINA SLATER I KNOW
AND OCCASIONALLY WISH I WAS

07:15.800 --> 07:17.000
DOES NOT THROW IN THE TOWEL

07:17.000 --> 07:18.500
JUST BECAUSE
THE OLD MAN SHE'S SCAMMING

07:18.500 --> 07:21.700
<i>HAS SUDDENLY GONE ALL SOFT
FOR HIS TRAMNESIAC DAUGHTER.</i>

07:21.700 --> 07:22.700
YOU'RE TOUCHING ME.

07:22.700 --> 07:23.900
IT WAS A RISK.
OH.

07:24.900 --> 07:27.300
I JUST DIDN'T COUNT ON
THE FATHER/DAUGHTER REBONDING.

07:27.300 --> 07:30.700
I HATE THAT LOVE WON OUT.
WELL, MAYBE SOMEONE SHOULD
REMIND DADDY'S LITTLE GIRL

07:30.700 --> 07:32.300
THAT SHE HATES DADDY,
AND THAT SHE SPENT

07:32.300 --> 07:34.400
THE LAST TWO YEARS
TRYING TO BRING HIM DOWN.

07:34.800 --> 07:37.700
WAIT A MINUTE.
AAH!

07:38.900 --> 07:41.200
OH, DID I SAY SOMETHING SMART?
I LOVE IT WHEN I DO THAT.

07:41.200 --> 07:43.600
HOW ARE YOU AT PHOTOSHOP?
A-MAH-ZING.

07:43.600 --> 07:45.300
I'M ABOUT TO REWRITE HISTORY.

07:48.500 --> 07:50.700
THIS SURE BEATS A 40-OUNCE.

07:50.700 --> 07:53.500
THE WEDDING'S POSTPONED.
DO YOU KNOW WHAT THIS MEANS?

07:53.500 --> 07:56.500
WILHELMINA IS LOSING
HER GRIP ON BRADFORD.

07:56.500 --> 07:59.200
WHY WE GOTTA TALK ABOUT HIM
DURING FAMILY TIME?

08:00.000 --> 08:02.200
I MADE THIS RUM PUNCH
OUT OF POMEGRANATE.

08:02.200 --> 08:03.500
THERE AIN'T NO MORE GUAVA.

08:03.500 --> 08:07.200
YOGA, PLEASE. IF I'M EVER
GOING TO GET HIM BACK, IT'S NOW.

08:07.600 --> 08:09.200
I'VE GOT TO GO
TO THAT BALL TONIGHT.

08:09.200 --> 08:10.400
I'VE GOT TO TALK TO HIM.

08:10.400 --> 08:13.500
YOU A WANTED FELON.
CINDERELLA CAN'T GO TO NO BALL.

08:14.500 --> 08:16.700
SHE CAN
IF IT'S A MASKED BALL.

08:22.300 --> 08:24.700
OH, HEY! UH,
I'M GLAD YOU'RE STILL HERE.

08:24.700 --> 08:27.500
THERE'S JUST A LITTLE PROBLEM
WITH MY SANDWICH.

08:27.500 --> 08:29.300
OH, MAN. IS THERE A HAIR?

08:29.600 --> 08:32.400
I'M, LIKE, THE ONLY ONE LEFT
IN MY FAMILY WITH A FULL HEAD.

08:33.500 --> 08:36.799
UH, NO. IT'S JUST THAT THERE ARE
ONLY THREE SUN-DRIED TOMATOES.

08:36.799 --> 08:39.000
YEAH. YEAH, I KNOW.
I MADE IT.

08:39.100 --> 08:40.200
OH, OKAY.

08:40.600 --> 08:43.600
UH, IT'S JUST THAT ROBERT
WOULD ALWAYS PUT MORE,

08:44.000 --> 08:44.600
SO...

08:46.400 --> 08:48.300
SORRY. I DON'T KNOW
WHERE ROBERT IS.

08:48.300 --> 08:49.600
I'M NOT HIS KEEPER, OKAY?

08:49.600 --> 08:52.300
BUT ROBERT DIDN'T KNOW JACK
ABOUT FOOD.

08:52.300 --> 08:54.600
A SUN-DRIED TOMATO
IS A CONCENTRATED FLAVOR.

08:54.600 --> 08:56.400
MORE THAN THREE
ON A SANDWICH

08:56.400 --> 08:58.800
WOULD OVERWHELM
THE SMOKY FLAVOR OF THE TURKEY.

08:58.800 --> 09:02.300
OKAY, UH, YOU KNOW WHAT?
I THINK MY TURKEY CAN HANDLE IT.

09:02.300 --> 09:05.400
SO COULD I JUST PLEASE HAVE
SOME MORE SUN-DRIED TOMATOES?

09:07.000 --> 09:07.900
NAH.

09:08.400 --> 09:09.400
IT WOULD BE WRONG.

09:09.400 --> 09:12.500
I-I WANT MY SANDWICH
THE WAY I WANT MY SANDWICH.

09:13.000 --> 09:13.800
WOW.

09:15.700 --> 09:17.800
(chuckles) YOU KNOW,
WHEN I FIRST SAW YOU,

09:18.100 --> 09:19.900
I THOUGHT, "WOW. THERE GOES
A GIRL FROM THE NEIGHBORHOOD.

09:19.900 --> 09:21.200
WHAT IS SHE DOING HERE?"

09:21.700 --> 09:25.200
NOW I SEE YOU'RE JUST LIKE ALL
THE OTHER SPOILED "MODE" GIRLS.

09:26.500 --> 09:28.400
NO. NO, I'M NOT!

09:28.400 --> 09:29.800
YOU KNOW, I BET
BEFORE YOU GOT HERE,

09:29.800 --> 09:32.200
YOU DIDN'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT A SUN-DRIED TOMATO WAS.

09:32.200 --> 09:33.800
YOU JUST REACHED INTO THE CART

09:33.800 --> 09:36.400
AND PULLED OUT WHATEVER
HAD THE MOST CHEESE.
I...

09:36.700 --> 09:38.200
I STILL EAT CHEESE.

09:38.200 --> 09:41.200
I MEAN, HOW DARE HE ACT
LIKE HE KNOWS WHO I AM?

09:41.200 --> 09:43.600
AND WH-WHY DO I EVEN HAVE
TO EXPLAIN MYSELF?

09:43.600 --> 09:47.800
OKAY, BETTY, NOT REALLY SURE
WHY YOU'RE SO UPSET.

09:48.100 --> 09:49.500
SUN-DRIED TOMATOES,
REALLY?

09:49.500 --> 09:52.700
I MEAN, DON'T YOU FIND THEM
KIND OF SALTY AND BREATHY?

09:52.700 --> 09:54.700
NO, IT'S NOT JUST THAT.
IT'S...

09:55.500 --> 09:57.300
I MEAN,
HE WAS SO RUDE TO ME.

09:57.300 --> 09:59.300
BETTY, YOU NEED
TO CALM DOWN, OKAY?

09:59.300 --> 10:01.600
I MEAN, GO ONLINE TO THAT--
THAT WEB SITE YOU LIKE.

10:01.600 --> 10:02.800
YOU KNOW,
THE ONE WITH THE BABY DUCKS

10:02.800 --> 10:04.200
WHO THINK THE CAT'S
THEIR MOTHER?

10:04.200 --> 10:07.500
socuteitssick.com--
I LOVE THAT WEB SITE.

10:08.300 --> 10:10.300
EXCEPT ONE OF THE BABY DUCKS
IS MISSING.

10:12.000 --> 10:14.200
ALL RIGHT,
WHAT IS THIS GUY'S NAME?

10:14.200 --> 10:15.300
I DON'T KNOW.

10:15.300 --> 10:17.600
SOMETHING LAME, LIKE GIO.

10:20.700 --> 10:21.800
Come back for what?

10:21.800 --> 10:23.700
For a chance to run.

10:24.100 --> 10:26.700
<i>HEY, PAPI.
HAVE YOU BEEN WATCHING?</i>

10:26.700 --> 10:28.800
SEÑOR DELGADO'S
IN A LOT OF TROUBLE.

10:28.800 --> 10:30.000
DO YOU THINK
THEY'RE GONNA KILL HIM?

10:30.000 --> 10:31.300
LET'S HOPE NOT.
(gun cocks)

10:31.600 --> 10:33.100
HEY, DID YOU BOOK
YOUR FLIGHT YET?

10:33.100 --> 10:37.300
NOT YET. I JUST WANTED
TO CALL AND SAY...

10:38.800 --> 10:39.600
I LOVE YOU ALL.

10:39.600 --> 10:41.300
<i>AY. YOU'RE SUCH
A NERVOUS FLYER.</i>

10:41.300 --> 10:44.400
IT'S GONNA BE FINE.
OOH, IT IS GETTING GOOD.

10:44.400 --> 10:46.700
OKAY, I'LL TALK TO YOU LATER.
LOVE YOU, BYE.

10:47.800 --> 10:52.200
YOU SEE? I'M NOT SUCH A MONSTER.
I LET YOU SAY GOOD-BYE.

10:52.200 --> 10:53.700
AT LEAST TELL ME
WHAT YOU WANT.

10:54.800 --> 10:55.900
WHO ARE YOU?
(door opens)

10:57.200 --> 10:59.000
(man) I THINK YOU KNOW
MY FATHER.

11:09.200 --> 11:11.500
RAMIRO VASQUEZ.

11:11.500 --> 11:13.400
IT SEEMS YOU DID NOT KILL ME
AFTER ALL.

11:15.200 --> 11:16.900
UH, NO,
FRIDAY DOESN'T REALLY HELP ME.

11:16.900 --> 11:19.300
I REALLY NEED TO GET
THE WHEELCHAIR HERE TONIGHT.

11:20.600 --> 11:22.400
WELL, THIS THING
CAN WALK AND TALK.

11:22.400 --> 11:23.600
CAN'T YOU JUST STICK IT
ON THE TURNPIKE

11:23.600 --> 11:26.000
AND GIVE IT MONEY FOR TOLLS?
THANK YOU.

11:26.000 --> 11:28.000
OKAY,
SO YOU DON'T GET SARCASM.

11:28.000 --> 11:29.500
COULD YOU PLEASE
JUST HOLD IT FOR ME,

11:29.500 --> 11:31.400
AND I-I PROMISE
I WILL FIND A WAY TO--

11:31.400 --> 11:34.500
<i>WELL, YOU MUST BE HAPPY</i>

11:34.500 --> 11:37.300
UM, I'LL CALL YOU BACK.
WHY?

11:37.300 --> 11:39.200
I JUST GOT FIRED

11:39.200 --> 11:41.700
<i>BECAUSE YOU WENT CRYING
TO YOUR BOSS.</i>

11:41.700 --> 11:43.200
NOW I DON'T HAVE A JOB.

11:44.600 --> 11:46.600
OH, MAN. I'M GONNA HAVE
TO GO BACK TO STEALING CABLE

11:46.600 --> 11:49.800
FROM MY NEIGHBOR,
WHICH I DON'T FEEL RIGHT ABOUT,

11:50.600 --> 11:52.700
ALL BECAUSE
SOME LITTLE "MODE" GIRL

11:52.700 --> 11:54.300
WASN'T HAPPY
WITH HER SANDWICH.

11:54.300 --> 11:56.900
NO, LOOK, I WASN'T TRYING
TO GET YOU FIRED. I WAS JUST--

11:56.900 --> 11:58.900
YEAH, WELL,
NONETHELESS, YOU DID.

12:00.500 --> 12:03.500
ALL RIGHT, EVERYBODY,
THAT'S IT FOR ME,

12:04.400 --> 12:06.000
BUT BEFORE I GO,

12:06.000 --> 12:09.700
THERE IS NO SUCH THING
AS FAT-FREE MAYO.

12:10.000 --> 12:15.100
THERE'S 125 CALORIES OF PURE FAT
PER TABLESPOON,

12:15.100 --> 12:17.800
<i>AND I PUT TWO IN EVERY SANDWICH.</i>

12:17.800 --> 12:18.600
OOH!

12:20.700 --> 12:22.100
SEE YOU AROUND,

12:23.000 --> 12:24.200
"MODE" GIRL.

12:25.200 --> 12:26.300
(Marc) NICE, BETTY.

12:26.600 --> 12:28.400
YOU'RE FINALLY ONE OF US.

